        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 6:39PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 638 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pueblo Depot, or 13 miles east of Pueblo Airport. This thunderstorm
was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo Depot.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
